HEADWORD: Grogginess
<hw>Grog"gi*ness</hw> <pr>(gr⟦ocr⟧g"g⟦icr⟧*n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>State of being groggy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Man.)</fld> <def>Tenderness or stiffness in the
foot of a horse, which causes him to move in a hobbling
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groggy</ent>⟦br⟧
